genresAdvancedInfo.name: estonian jazz
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Estonian jazz is a blend of traditional jazz elements with folk music influences. It often features complex rhythms and improvisation, with a focus on showcasing the individual talents of the musicians. Estonian metal is known for its heavy, distorted guitar riffs and aggressive vocals. It often incorporates elements of folk music and mythology, creating a unique sound that is both powerful and atmospheric. Estonian pop is characterized by catchy melodies and upbeat rhythms, with a focus on radio-friendly hooks and sing-along choruses. It often draws inspiration from international pop trends, while also incorporating elements of traditional Estonian music.
